  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study aimed to compare the efficacy of pin-tract infection prevention between
      silversulfadiazine and dry dressing.

      Methods: 30 patients with an open tibial fracture admitted to Songklanagarind hospital from
      September 2007 to June 2008 and treated by emergency debridement and external fixation were
      randomized into two groups, one treated with silversulfadiazine for infection prophylaxis
      (15) and a control group treated with dry dressing only (15). All patients were followed
      until the external fixator was removed. Pin-site infections were assessed and graded at each
      follow-up visit by an orthopaedist blinded to the mode of treatment. A culture from the pin
      site was done if an infection occurred.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
